<% content_for :title, "Search Icons Tool" %>
<% content_for :subtitle do %>
    Intelligent semantic search for Lucide React icons using natural language
<% end %>

<%= h2_with_anchor "Overview" %>

<p>Langgraph Feature (not Rails): </p>

<p>The <code>SearchIconsTool</code> is a LangChain-compatible tool that enables AI agents to find appropriate icons from the Lucide React library using natural language queries. Unlike traditional keyword search, this tool understands concepts, visual descriptions, and intended use cases.</p>

<div class="alert alert-success">
    <p><strong>Key Features:</strong></p>
    <ul>
        <li>Semantic understanding of icon concepts</li>
        <li>Visual description matching ("three horizontal lines" → menu icon)</li>
        <li>Action-based queries ("save to disk" → save icon)</li>
        <li>Parallel multi-query execution</li>
        <li>Intelligent result caching</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<%= h2_with_anchor "How It Works" %>

<p>The tool leverages vector embeddings to understand the semantic meaning behind icon queries:</p>

<pre><code class="language-mermaid">
graph TD
    A[Natural Language Query] --> B[SearchIconsTool]
    B --> C[SearchIconsService]
    C --> D[PostgresEmbeddingsService]
    D --> E[Vector Similarity Search]
    E --> F[Lucide Icons Database]
    F --> G[Ranked Icon Results]
    G --> H[Return Icon Names]
</code></pre>

<%= h2_with_anchor "Usage Examples" %>

<%= h3_with_anchor "Basic Icon Search" %>

<pre><code class="language-typescript">const searchIconsTool = new SearchIconsTool();

// Single query search
const result = await searchIconsTool.invoke({
    queries: ["user authentication"],
    limit: 5
});

console.log(result.results);
// {
//   "user authentication": ["user", "lock", "key", "shield", "user-check"]
// }</code></pre>

<%= h3_with_anchor "Multi-Query Search" %>

<pre><code class="language-typescript">// Search for multiple icon types in parallel
const result = await searchIconsTool.invoke({
    queries: [
        "navigation menu",
        "save document", 
        "delete item",
        "user profile"
    ],
    limit: 3
});

console.log(result.results);
// {
